	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>886 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.75]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>For all the good the DEX and AGI will do you get a Fungi Tunic (you almost have enough money for one).&nbsp;&nbsp;The regen is better than the Iksar chest plate.<br><br>Focus on STR, AC and HP gear.  I can't begin to express my amazement how much difference a couple of hundred extra HP and about 20 AC make at level 48!  DEX is only good for proc'ing weapons and relying on proc's is just asking for a quick 'LOADING. PLEASE WAIT.'<br><br>Silver Chitin Handwraps are a good suggestion.  <br><br>Guilds are a matter of personal taste.  Different guilds have different emphasis on playing style. Most seem to be geared to the higher end game where you need guilds for planar raids.  Some are geared more to the casual player just looking for experience groups.  Some guilds are very restrictive about their membership requirements. Others will take anyone with a pulse.  You have to try grouping with some guilded players.  If you like the way they play the ask if you can join their guild.  You can always quit if you decide the guild is not the right fit.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
