	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=125152><span id= >Rollander</span></a><br><span id=notbold>457 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.93]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'd say grab STR gear right off.&nbsp;&nbsp;STR = ATK with the added bonus of being able to carry more loot (never underestimate that).  Your second stat to raise might be DEX, but that's up to you.  A regen item is nice, but you're not much for soloing, and in an ideal situation, you don't take that much damage.  <br><br>What you might do is sell that Belt and buy Silver Chitin Handwraps.  The price difference should come out quite in your favor and the stats on SCHW are more suited for you - same haste % also.  The Silvery Belt of Contention is well liked by Hybrid classes because of the WIS and INT bonuses, and sells pretty well.<br><br>If that trade works out like it should, you should have a few kpp freed up for some STR gear like a Hero Bracer, Spider Fur Belt, etc.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Jan  5 19:34:31 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br>-----------------------<br>Rogues do it from behind.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276</a> <br>Tyrlinoth Arkonnen &lt;Legendary Chaos&gt; - EQ's Drunkest Guild<br>The Nameless</td></td></tr>
